This article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence and Taoiseach Leo Varadkar during a breakfast event at the Vice President's Residence in Washington, D.C. They discussed the strong relationship between Ireland and the United States and the contributions of Irish immigrants to America. They also mentioned the importance of the Good Friday Agreement and the need for peace in Northern Ireland. Varadkar expressed his support for a free-trade agreement between the EU and the US to further strengthen economic ties. The remarks concluded with Varadkar thanking Pence for his hospitality and inviting him to visit Ireland in the future.